1️⃣ Fork the repository

Go to the original repository: Codecademy/wedding-rsvp-off-platform-project

Click the Fork button at the top-right corner.

This creates a copy of the repository under your GitHub account.

2️⃣ Clone your forked repository locally

On your forked repo page, click the Code button to get the SSH or HTTPS URL.

In your terminal, run:

git clone git@github.com:<your-username>/wedding-rsvp-off-platform-project.git


Replace <your-username> with your GitHub username.

Navigate into the cloned repository:

cd wedding-rsvp-off-platform-project

3️⃣ Create a new branch

Make a branch specifically for your RSVP changes:

git checkout -b rsvp-yourname


Replace yourname with your name or identifier. This switches you to the new branch immediately.

4️⃣ Update guests.md

Open the file guests.md in your editor.

Add a new row in the Markdown table with your name and the number of guests coming with you. Example:

| Name        | Guests |
|-------------|--------|
| Your Name   | 2      |


Save the file.

5️⃣ Stage and commit your changes

Stage the updated file:

git add guests.md


Commit your changes with a descriptive message:

git commit -m "Added my name and guest count to the RSVP list"

6️⃣ Push your branch to GitHub

Push your rsvp-yourname branch to your forked repository:

git push origin rsvp-yourname

7️⃣ Create a pull request

Go to your forked repository on GitHub.

You’ll see a prompt to Compare & pull request for the branch you just pushed.

Click it.

Update the title to something descriptive, e.g.,:

Add RSVP for Your Name


Ensure the description explains your changes (GitHub may auto-fill a template).

Check all the boxes in the checklist if applicable.

Click Create pull request.
